09/07/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH Federation House of Peoples adopted the penal code and the criminal proceedings law on Tuesday (8 July). 
Lawmakers say the measures are consistent with EU standards and practice and meet recommendations of international financial institutions for streamlining judicial reforms.
Also Tuesday, the IMF published a series of documents aimed at encouraging sustainable economic growth, prudent fiscal policy and structural reforms in BiH, including strengthening of the judicial system.
In other news, BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic met Tuesday with a delegation from Macedonia led by his counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski. 
The meeting focused on expanding economic relations. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Dnevni List - 09/07/03; BHTV1, BBC, IMF Web site, Onasa, MIA - 08/07/03)
